<% content_for :title, "HoneyOps | Cookie Policy" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Cookie policy for HoneyOps, detailing essential session and security cookies and how to manage them." %>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-slate-950 text-slate-100">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-4xl">
      Cookie Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">
      Last updated: 2025
    </p>

    <p class="mt-6 text-slate-300">
      This website (honeyops.net and related subdomains) uses only
      strictly necessary cookies to ensure the technical operation and security of the
      HoneyOps platform. We do not use cookies for advertising, behavioural tracking,
      or advanced analytics.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">
      1. What are cookies?
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300">
      Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device when you visit a
      website. They help websites remember information about your visit, such as your
      session or preferences, so that the site can function correctly.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">
      2. Cookies we use
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300">
      HoneyOps uses only essential cookies required for the provision of the service:
    </p>

    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300">
      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">Session cookie</span>
        (e.g. <code class="text-amber-300">_honeyops_session</code>):
        used to keep you logged in securely to the HoneyOps console.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">Security cookies</span>
        (such as CSRF-related tokens): used to protect forms and logins against abuse
        and fraudulent activity.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300">
      These cookies are classified as <span class="font-medium">strictly necessary</span>
      and do not require your consent under EU law, as they are essential for providing
      the service you actively request (secure access to the HoneyOps platform).
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">
      3. Cookies we do not use
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300">
      HoneyOps does <span class="font-semibold">not</span> use:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-slate-300 text-sm">
      <li>Advertising or marketing cookies.</li>
      <li>Advanced analytics cookies (such as Google Analytics, Matomo, etc.).</li>
      <li>Social media tracking pixels or similar technologies.</li>
      <li>Browser fingerprinting or equivalent tracking methods.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">
      4. Managing cookies in your browser
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300">
      You can configure your browser to block or delete cookies at any time. However,
      if you disable essential cookies, parts of the HoneyOps platform (including the
      login process) may no longer function correctly.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">
      5. Contact
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300">
      If you have any questions about this Cookie Policy, please contact us at:
      <a href="mailto:privacy@honeyops.net" class="text-amber-400 hover:underline">
        info@honeyops.net
      </a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
